    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200\u00b0C/ 180\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 6 and boil a kettle</p><p>Cut narrow slices (about the width of a pound coin) into your <strong>waxy potatoes</strong>, making sure not to cut all the way down to the base \u2013 these are your <strong>hasselback potatoes</strong></p><p>Tip: Rest the potatoes in the hollow of a wooden spoon when cutting, it will prevent you from cutting all the way through the potato!</p><p>Add the <strong>hasselback potatoes</strong> to a baking tray (or two!), drizzle with <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and<strong> pepper</strong></p><p>Strip the <strong>thyme leaves</strong>, discarding the stems and sprinkle the leaves over the potatoes</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for an initial 20 minutes</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/duck-breast-with-hasselback-potatoes-and-caramelised-shallot-and-fig-jus/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Pat your <strong>duck breast[s]</strong> dry with kitchen paper, then using a sharp knife, score the <strong>duck skin</strong> on a diagonal, being careful not to cut through to the meat</p><p>Season the duck skin with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Heat a large, dry, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>scored duck</strong> to the pan, skin-side down and cook for 3-4 min on each side, or until the skin<strong> </strong>is golden and crisp</p><p>Tip: Cooking for 3 or more? Use 2 pans!</p><p>Reserve the <strong>duck fat</strong> for your potatoes and reserve the pan</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/duck-breast-with-hasselback-potatoes-and-caramelised-shallot-and-fig-jus/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>golden duck breast</strong> to another baking tray skin side up</p><p>Put the tray in the oven and cook for 10-12 min further or until the duck is cooked through \u2013 this is your <strong>roasted duck breast</strong></p><p>Tip: Cooking for 3 or more? Use 2 trays!</p><p>Once ready, transfer the <strong>roasted duck breast</strong> to a clean chopping board to rest</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/duck-breast-with-hasselback-potatoes-and-caramelised-shallot-and-fig-jus/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the potatoes have been in for 20 minutes, remove the tray from the oven and drizzle the <strong>reserved duck fat</strong> all over</p><p>Return the tray to the oven for 15-20 minutes further or until the potatoes tender and crispy \u2013 these are your <strong>hasselback potatoes</strong></p><p>While the duck and potatoes cook, peel and slice your <strong>shallots </strong>in half</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/duck-breast-with-hasselback-potatoes-and-caramelised-shallot-and-fig-jus/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Heat a pot with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>shallot halves</strong>, cut side down and cook for 3-4 minutes or until starting to caramelise</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/duck-breast-with-hasselback-potatoes-and-caramelised-shallot-and-fig-jus/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once caramelised, add your <strong>bay leaf[ves] </strong>and <strong>gravy base </strong>with 125ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[200ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[250ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and<strong> pepper </strong>and cook for 2-3 min, stirring regularly, or until thickened</p><p>Once thickened, remove the<strong> bay leaves</strong> and discard</p><p>Stir in the <strong>fig relish</strong> and with a knob of <strong>butter</strong> and cook for 1 min further or until thick and glossy \u2013 this is your<strong> caramelised shallot & fig jus</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/duck-breast-with-hasselback-potatoes-and-caramelised-shallot-and-fig-jus/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely slice your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Return the reserved pan to a medium heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once melted, add the <strong>sliced garlic</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and<strong> pepper</strong> and cook for 1-2 minutes or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>Tenderstem broccoli </strong>with a splash of<strong> boiled water</strong> and cook, covered, for 4-5 min or until tender with a slight bite \u2013 this is your <strong>garlicky Tenderstem</strong></p><p>Tip: Drain any excess water from your broccoli before serving</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/duck-breast-with-hasselback-potatoes-and-caramelised-shallot-and-fig-jus/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Slice the <strong>rested duck</strong> finely, on the diagonal</p><p>Serve the <strong>sliced duck </strong>with the <strong>hasselback potatoes</strong> and <strong>garlic Tenderstem broccoli</strong> to the side</p><p>Spoon over the <strong>caramelised shallot & fig jus</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
